# No Hardcoded Localhost URLs

Application source code must never contain hardcoded `localhost`, `127.0.0.1`, or other loopback URLs. Use Angular environment configuration so the correct base URL is resolved at build time.

## Forbidden in application source (*.ts, *.html, *.scss)

- `http://localhost` or `https://localhost` (with or without a port)
- `http://127.0.0.1` or `https://127.0.0.1`
- `http://0.0.0.0` or `https://0.0.0.0`

## Where localhost IS allowed

- `src/environments/environment.ts` — this is the **dev-only** config and is swapped out at build time
- Proxy config files (`proxy.conf.json`, `proxy.conf.js`)
- Test files (`*.spec.ts`, `*.test.ts`, `e2e/**`)
- Documentation text explaining local dev setup (e.g. `documentation.ts`)
- Docker / CI config files
- Storybook config (`.storybook/**`)

## How it works in this project

External URLs (e.g. Storybook links) are driven by `src/environments/environment.ts`:

```typescript
// src/environments/environment.ts (dev — used by ng serve)
export const environment = {
    production: false,
    storybookBaseUrl: 'http://localhost:6006'
};

// src/environments/environment.prod.ts (prod — used by ng build)
export const environment = {
    production: true,
    storybookBaseUrl: ''
};
```

Components import and use the environment constant:

```typescript
import { environment } from '../../../environments/environment';
const SB = environment.storybookBaseUrl;

// Then in menu items:
{ label: 'Avatar', url: `${SB}/?path=/docs/components-datadisplay-avatar--docs` }
```

## Pre-commit check

Before committing, scan staged files (excluding allowed locations) for violations:

```bash
git diff --cached --name-only \
  | grep -v 'environment\.ts' \
  | grep -v 'proxy\.conf' \
  | grep -v '\.spec\.ts' \
  | grep -v '\.storybook' \
  | xargs grep -nE 'https?://(localhost|127\.0\.0\.1|0\.0\.0\.0)' || true
```

If matches are found, **stop the commit**, list every occurrence, and suggest moving the URL into environment config.
